                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15a4/372: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-11T23:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 11, 1931—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 11—10:09 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>124. My 121, September 10, 9 p.m.<note n="54" xml:id="d328fn54">Not
                        printed.</note> Danish delegation has introduced a resolution of which the
                    positive part reads as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The Assembly begs the Council to bring its influence to bear on the
                            Governments attending the said Conference in order that they may give
                            proof of their firm desire to bring about a successful conclusion of the
                            efforts to insure peace and to reestablish mutual confidence by
                            abstaining, pending the final result of the Conference, from any measure
                            having as its object an increase of the actual present level of their
                            armaments and from causing thereby an increase in their budgets.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>The Italian delegation is not satisfied with this form and desires in this
                    connection direct reference of this matter to the Third Committee for
                    discussion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
